  description="South Africa's grand strategy — analysis, critique, and realignment — and how the GovCompass Reform Agenda provides the domestic execution layer on which it depends."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <header class="mb-10">
    <p
      class="font-heading text-sm font-semibold text-compass-green uppercase tracking-wide mb-2"
    >
      Topic — Grand Strategy
    </p>
    <h1
      class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-3 leading-tight"
    >
      Constitutional Non-Alignment for a Multipolar Era
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
      South Africa's grand strategy — analysis, critique, and realignment — and
      how the GovCompass Reform Agenda provides the domestic execution layer on
      which it depends.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
      This is the synthesis article for the Topics section. It reconstructs
      South Africa's grand strategy from its doctrinal stack, evaluates it
      through the classical Ends–Ways–Means triad, and proposes an
      endowment-aligned alternative. It then shows, explicitly, how every pillar
      of the GovCompass Reform Agenda maps to a component of that grand strategy
      — so that readers who have worked through the five Topic pillars can see
      exactly how domestic reform plugs into national strategic ambition.
    </p>

    <div
      class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-text-secondary font-heading border-t border-gray-200 pt-4"
    >
      <span>Citizen X</span>
      <time datetime={publishDate.toISOString()}>{formattedDate}</time>
      <span aria-label={`${readingTime} minute read`}
        >{readingTime} min read</span
      >
    </div>
  </header>

  <JumpToSection links={jumpLinks} class="mb-12" />

  <!-- Reading-level note -->
  <Callout type="takeaway">
    <p class="mb-2">
      <strong>This is the long-form synthesis</strong> — pitched at the policy-analyst
      end of GovCompass, and the bridge between the five Topic pillars and the Reform
      Agenda. Plan for a long sitting, or jump to the section you need.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-2">
      <strong
        >If you want the citizen-pitched version of the same argument:</strong
      > skip to
      <a href="#summary" class="text-compass-green underline font-semibold"
        >In plain English</a
      > below (90 seconds), then to
      <a href="#conclusion" class="text-compass-green underline font-semibold"
        >What this means for citizens</a
      >
